gobblin.source.extractor

Enum JobCommitPolicy

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<JobCommitPolicy>
      • gobblin.source.extractor.JobCommitPolicy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<JobCommitPolicy>

    public enum JobCommitPolicy
extends Enum<JobCommitPolicy>
    An enumeration of policies on how output data of jobs/tasks should be committed.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      COMMIT_ON_FULL_SUCCESS
      Commit output data of a job if and only if all of its tasks successfully complete.
      COMMIT_ON_PARTIAL_SUCCESS
      Deprecated. 
      Use COMMIT_SUCCESSFUL_TASKS instead, which provides a less confusing commit semantics, and should cover most use cases when COMMIT_ON_FULL_SUCCESS is not appropriate.
      COMMIT_SUCCESSFUL_TASKS
      Commit output data of tasks that successfully complete.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • COMMIT_ON_FULL_SUCCESS

        public static final JobCommitPolicy COMMIT_ON_FULL_SUCCESS
        Commit output data of a job if and only if all of its tasks successfully complete.

      • COMMIT_ON_PARTIAL_SUCCESS

        @Deprecated
public static final JobCommitPolicy COMMIT_ON_PARTIAL_SUCCESS
        Deprecated. Use COMMIT_SUCCESSFUL_TASKS instead, which provides a less confusing commit semantics, and should cover most use cases when COMMIT_ON_FULL_SUCCESS is not appropriate.
        Commit a job even if some of its tasks fail. It's up to the DataPublisher to decide whether data of failed tasks of the job should be committed or not.

      • COMMIT_SUCCESSFUL_TASKS

        public static final JobCommitPolicy COMMIT_SUCCESSFUL_TASKS
        Commit output data of tasks that successfully complete. It is recommended to use this commit policy in conjunction with task-level data publishing (i.e., when ConfigurationKeys.PUBLISH_DATA_AT_JOB_LEVEL is set to false).
